                            <comment id="13093369" author="jkreps" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 01:53:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can a brother get a +1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13093667" author="bmatheny" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 12:00:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Appreciate the comment cleanup. The System.out.flush() line looks like it has a different indentation level than the other lines in the same block. Everything else looks good. Not sure if a +1 is required from Kafka devs or not but it has my vote.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13095065" author="junrao" created="Thu, 1 Sep 2011 01:32:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; the patch looks good to me. +1 please fix the indentation before checking in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13095101" author="jjkoshy" created="Thu, 1 Sep 2011 03:46:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PrintStream javadoc suggests that System.out.flush() is redundant, since checkError also does a flush. Per our coding conventions since checkError has that side-effect, optional parentheses would be appropriate for that call.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
